# PhantomLoot

A TBC (2.4.3) loot management addon for World of Warcraft: The Burning Crusade. PhantomLoot automates item rolling and soft reservation in raid environments, integrating with [softres.it](https://softres.it) for soft-res list management.

Originally based on [RollFor](https://github.com/sica42/RollFor) by Obszczymucha.

---

## Features

- **Automated rolling** — starts and manages rolls in chat, detects results, resolves ties automatically
- **Soft reservation integration** — imports SR data from softres.it; minimap icon shows at a glance who hasn't soft-ressed
- **Master loot support** — enhanced master loot window with candidates sorted by class, confirmation dialogs, and automated loot method detection
- **Raid roll** — randomizes loot among eligible players (`/rr`)
- **Insta raid roll** — instant no-countdown raid roll (`/irr`)
- **Winner tracking** — tracks all loot awarded in a session with a popup history view
- **Trade tracking** — monitors trades after loot is awarded and updates records accordingly
- **+1 system** — track bonus rolls awarded to players (`/pl`)
- **Auto loot** — configurable automatic looting behavior
- **Version broadcast** — checks which raiders are running PhantomLoot and which version

---

## Requirements

- World of Warcraft: The Burning Crusade (interface version 20400 / patch 2.4.3)
- [softres.it](https://softres.it) account for soft reservation lists (free)

---

## Installation

1. Download or clone this repository
2. Rename the folder to `PhantomLoot` if it isn't already
3. Place the `PhantomLoot` folder in your addons directory:
   ```
   World of Warcraft\_tbc_\Interface\AddOns\PhantomLoot\
   ```
4. Launch the game and enable PhantomLoot in the AddOns menu on the character select screen

---

## Soft Reservation Setup

PhantomLoot uses [softres.it](https://softres.it) as its soft-res backend.

1. Create a raid at softres.it and share the link with your raiders
2. Once everyone has reserved, lock the raid and click **Gargul Export**
3. Copy the exported string
4. In-game, open the SR import window (`/sr` or click the minimap button) and paste the string
5. PhantomLoot will auto-match player names and update the minimap icon

**Minimap icon colors:**
- 🟢 Green — everyone in the raid has soft-ressed
- 🟠 Orange — some players have not soft-ressed
- 🔴 Red — soft-res data is outdated
- ⚪ White — no soft-res data loaded

---

## Slash Commands

### Rolling
| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `/rf [item] [count] [seconds]` | Start a normal roll (respects soft-res) |
| `/arf [item] [count] [seconds]` | Start a roll ignoring soft-res (all roll) |
| `/rr [item]` | Raid roll — random winner among eligible players |
| `/irr [item]` | Insta raid roll — instant, no countdown |
| `/cr` | Cancel rolling in progress |
| `/fr` | Finish rolling early |
| `/ssr [limit]` | Show sorted rolls (default: top 5) |
| `/rfr` | Reset dropped loot announce |
| `/htr` | Announce how-to-roll instructions to the group |

### Soft Reservation
| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `/sr` | Open / close the soft-res import window |
| `/sr init` | Clear all soft-res data and reset |
| `/srs` | Show current soft-res list |
| `/src` | Check who hasn't soft-ressed |
| `/src a` | Announce missing soft-ressers in chat |
| `/src aw` | Announce missing soft-ressers as a raid warning |
| `/sro` | Manually match player names |

### Windows & Misc
| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `/rfw` | Open winner tracking popup |
| `/rfo` | Open options popup |
| `/pl` | List current +1's |
| `/pl add [player] [item]` | Add a +1 for a player |
| `/pl rm [player] [item]` | Remove a +1 from a player |
| `/rf versioncheck` | Check addon versions across the group |
| `/rf versioncheck guild` | Check addon versions across the guild |

---

## Key Bindings

PhantomLoot registers three bindable actions in the **Key Bindings** menu under the **PhantomLoot** header:

- Toggle options window
- Toggle SR import window
- Toggle winners window

---

## How Rolling Works

When you start a roll with `/rf [item]`, PhantomLoot:

1. Announces the item and roll window to the group
2. Watches chat for `/roll` results from eligible players
3. If the item is soft-ressed, only players who reserved it are eligible for the SR roll; others can roll offspec
4. Automatically detects ties and prompts a re-roll
5. Announces the winner and records the award

**Roll thresholds (default):**
- Main spec: `/roll` (1–100)
- Off spec: `/roll 99` (1–99)

---

## Saved Variables

PhantomLoot stores data in two places:

- `PhantomLootDb` — account-wide (awarded loot history, config, minimap position)
- `PhantomLootCharDb` — per-character (soft-res data, name matcher overrides)

These are saved in `WTF\Account\...\SavedVariables\` automatically.

